         </tr>
         <tr vAlign="top">
            <td colspan="1">$a - Chronological term (NR) <br>$v - Form subdivision (R) <br>$x - General subdivision (R) <br>$y - Chronological subdivision (R) <br></td>
            <td colspan="1">$z - Geographic subdivision (R) <br>$6 - Linkage (NR) <br>$8 - Field link and sequence number (R) <br></td>
         </tr>
   </table>
      <hr>
      <h3>FIELD DEFINITION AND SCOPE</h3>
      <p>In an established heading record, field 148 contains the established form of a
                     chronological term. In records for references, this field contains an unestablished form
                     of a chronological term.      </p>
      <hr>
      <h3>GUIDELINES FOR APPLYING CONTENT DESIGNATORS</h3>
      <p>Guidelines for applying the content designators defined for field 148 and input
                     conventions are given in the <em><a href="adx48.html">X48 Chronological Terms-General Information</a></em>
                     section.
      </p>
